stunned many residents of the central city here, but few have
expressed more dismay than an elderly gentleman on a poverty-pocked
block who has been monitoring the neighborhood's civic affairs
since the Great Depression. At 86, Frank P. Zeidler is the last of
Milwaukee's three Socialist mayors _ no other major American city
has had even one _ and a living link to a time when Wisconsin
politics was synonymous with safety-net expansions, like workers'
compensation and unemployment insurance. By Jason DeParle.
