 THE STYLE OF CLEAN TILE &AMP; GROUT 
 Includes a color photo of tiles, in JPEG format. Photo is
immediately available by calling William Gonzalez at 212-499-3355. 
 By CARY McMULLEN 
 c.1999 New York Times Regional Newspapers 
<TEXT>
 &UR; World rights &QL;
<P>
   Whether left in natural ceramic or covered with bright, primary
glazes, tile has become a fixture in contemporary homes due to its
durability and versatility. Tile is appealing to homeowners
specifically because it doesn't require much maintenance. Glazed
tile is virtually stain-proof. But what about the white, gritty
stuff in between the squares? Try these tips for keeping both tile
and grout looking great.
</P>
<P>
   (slugged: BC-TILE-CLEAN-LIFEBEAT-ART-NYTSF, priority code r,
category code l)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; AMAZON.COM'S JEFFREY P. BEZOS, LORD OF THE JUNGLE &QL; 
 &UR; By YLEANA MARTINEZ &QL; 
 &UR; c.1999 Hispanic magazine &QL; 
 &UR; World rights &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Jeffrey P. Bezos revolutionized book buying on-line with his
Internet company, Amazon.com. ``He tapped into a gold mine when he
began selling books on-line. Now his expanded and fast-growing
company is leading the way, and competitors are hot on his trail,''
writes Yleana Martinez in Hispanic magazine. Read how this
35-year-old son of a Cuban immigrant started up in 1995 the company
that today boasts 4.5 million customers in 160 countries. (slugged:
BC-AMAZON.COM'S-BEZOS-LIFEBEAT-NYTSF, priority code r, category
code l) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ARRANGED MARRIAGES: `THE LOVE WILL GROW' &QL; 
 &UR; By PRADNYA JOSHI &QL; 
 &UR; c.1999 A. magazine &QL;
</P>
<P>
   When it comes time to marry, should one speed up on the dating
track, or would an arranged marriage be the best route? This is the
question that Indian American women have to decide when
contemplating wedded union. Pradna Joshi in A. Magazine gives her
spin on the process. ``There are many second-generation Indian
Americans who find that the arranged marriage question travels
across the seas to perch persistently on their doorsteps,'' she
writes. She, however, is not entirely convinced by either course of
action. But secretly, she hopes love will win the debate in her own
case. (slugged: BC-ARRANGED-MARRIAGES-LIFEBEAT-NYTSF, priority code
r, category code l) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NAME YOUR PRICE &QL; 
 &UR; By CHRISENA COLEMAN &QL; 
 &UR; c. 1999 Black Elegance &QL; 
 &UR; World rights &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Out of the shadows, soul singer Kelly Price now commands center
stage. Chrisena Coleman talked to the 25-year-old singer,
songwriter and composer about her new album ``Soul of a Woman,''
and her struggles to shed pounds after critics told her she would
never make her mark until she did. ``I am happy being a thick Black
woman,'' Price told her. ``I always felt that God had a plan for me
and He did. He did it in His time, which is fine by me.'' (slugged:
BC-MUSIC:KELLY-PRICE-LIFEBEAT-NYTSF, priority code r, category code
l) &QL;
</P>
