</P>
<P>
   Q: In view of current military operations, I'm curious about
Defense Secretary William S. Cohen. I once heard that he served in
the National Guard. Do you know when, and in what unit or units?
What rank did he attain?
</P>
<P>
   A: Cohen, who was born in 1940, was never in the armed forces,
National Guard or otherwise. In 1988, when he was a Republican
senator from Maine on the Armed Services Committee, Cohen explained
how he avoided being drafted. ``I was exempt: college deferments
and so forth, all the way through,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   END
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
