Catahoula girl dog home from the vet this week after having her
fixed so as not to further perpetuate the species. I consider it my
contribution towards the betterment of mankind. (Murray, Cox News
Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   NETHAWAY-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ Animal terrorists finally forced
the removal of a ``Jesus was a vegetarian'' billboard in Amarillo,
Texas. Threats were made that animals would be mutilated if the
billboard wasn't taken down. The company that owns the billboard
space bowed to threats and public outcries and removed the message,
according to People for the Ethical Treatment of Animals, which put
up the billboard. axed letters to the editor from PETA attempted
get the word out in time for Easter Sunday that Jesus was a
vegetarian. After concluding its argument that Jesus ate only
vegetables, PETA's letter said, ``On Easter Sunday, please bless
the animals, not by saying grace over pieces of them on plates, but
by sharing a peaceful, loving vegetarian dinner.'' (Nethaway, Waco
Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   KELSO-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ In his Monday column, editorial
page editor Arnold Garcia Jr. accused me of falling ``into the
ranks of yuppiedom'' because I own a cell phone. Yeah, well, Arnold
Garcia is wearing a tie in his mug shot. (Kelso, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
