   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   PEEPING-TOMS (Sacramento, Calif.) _ California lawmakers have
made video peeping _ up women's skirts and down their blouses _ the
newest anti-crime crusade. More than 100 Web sites are devoted to
so-called ``upskirt'' voyeurism, where men with tiny cameras hang
out at shopping malls, amusement parks and beaches to secretly
videotape women's underwear, lingerie, pantyhose or whatever. By
ROBERT SALLADAY.
</P>
<P>
   NITRO-DRUG (Sacramento, Calif.) _ The state Legislature is
moving quickly to outlaw a euphoric elixir popular in San Francisco
dance clubs, after reports that dozens of people have become
seriously sick by ingesting the mood-enhancement drug. Sometimes
called Blue Nitro or Vitality, the designer potion is supposed to
lift your mood, boost your sex life, even burn fat and give you a
decent night's sleep. By ROBERT SALLADAY.
</P>
<P>
   ESTATE-POOR (San Francisco) _ The $5.1 million estate bequeathed
to the city by a reclusive Polish immigrant will create a perpetual
fund for aiding poor and elderly San Franciscans under a plan
approved by a Board of Supervisors committee. By ERIC BRAZIL.
</P>
