   INSULIN-INHALE (San Francisco) _ Millions of diabetics who must
inject themselves with insulin several times a day could find
relief in a product made by Inhale Therapeutic Systems Inc. in San
Carlos, Calif. The firm has developed a technology to deliver drugs
like insulin by inhalation rather than injection. By JUDY RICHTER.
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT (``e'' category)
</P>
<P>
   FILM-HEDDA-GABLER (Franklin, N.Y.) _ Working on a shoestring
budget, friends and family are turning Henrik Ibsen's subtle,
brutal play ``Hedda Gabler'' into a film. ``It comes across to me
as an unbelievably modern play the way it sort of strikes into an
existential dilemma,'' says director David Bridel. By AMY
BIANCOLLI.
</P>
<P>
   TV-REVIEW-COMEDY (Undated) _ Comedy Central is under a unique
kind of pressure in that the channel has to be funny _ after all,
that's the name of the damn network. Bearing this burden, Comedy
Central offers us ``Strangers with Candy.'' the channel's latest
effort in translating weird into funny. Unfortunately, ``Strangers
with Candy'' is speaking French and it comes out Dutch. By TIM
GOODMAN.
</P>
<P>
   TV-REVIEW-GRACE (Undated) _ The last few TV seasons have not
been kind to sitcoms. And, with their predictable insert-joke-here
moments and embarrassing laugh tracks, sitcoms have not been kind
to viewers. But then there's ``Will &AMP; Grace.'' By TIM GOODMAN.
