<TEXT>
<P>
   ATTN SPORTS EDITORS
</P>
<P>
   Cox News Service is marking the 25th anniversary of Hank Aaron's
breaking of the home run mark with a package of stories and photos.
Aaron hit his 715th home run in Atlanta on April 8, 1974, to break
Babe Ruth's record.
</P>
<P>
   Two photos, one a new color portrait of Aaron and the other
showing him circling the bases after the record home run, are
moving from the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   Below are stories that will move today for publication Thursday.
Note that two of the stories moved last week as part of the Cox
baseball preview.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-HANK-CHASE _ ATLANTA _ Those who were around 25 years ago
during Hank Aaron's chase of Babe Ruth's all-time HR record try to
describe how that event would have been different had it taken
place today. (Rosen, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). MOVED
(Originally moved last week as part of Cox's baseball preview.)
</P>
<P>
   BBO-HANK-BALL _ ATLANTA _ The ball, the bat, the uniform from
Hank Aaron's chase of Ruth. Where are they and what would they be
worth on today's memorabilia market? (Rosen, Atlanta
Journal-Constituion). MOVED (Originally moved last week as part of
Cox's baseball preview.)
</P>
<P>
   BBO-HANK-HAMMER _ ATLANTA _ The Transformation of the Hammer: He
has gone from apolitical, backwoods superstar to star-crossed
middle-aged activist to the senior statesman of baseball. The Hank
Aaron that will be honored tonight on the 25th anniversary of his
career home-run record is a kindler, gentler Aaron, who has been
portrayed in any number of ways. (Stinson, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) ETA: 6 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-HANK-BUSINESSES _ ATLANTA _ Hank Aaron is expanding his
outside business interests. Already the owner of several Church's
Fried Chicken stores, he's also opening a BMW dealership. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) ETA: 6 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   BBOP-HANK-LIST _ Hank Aaron's home-run list. ETA: 6 p.m.
</P>
