if Milosevic did not give in?
</P>
<P>
   Why do we only now learn about the prospect of a ``long war,''
perhaps lasting four years?
</P>
<P>
   And why, for God's sake, did no one _ not President Bill
Clinton, not NATO's Secretary-General Javier Solana, nor Robin
Cook, nor General Wesley Clark _ realize that bombing must be
supported by ground troops?
</P>
<P>
   How on earth did Clark come to believe that the Serbs would give
up so easily? Did he mistake the Yugoslav army for the Serb
