   INVASION-SCENARIOS (Washington) _ Two visions are emerging for
an allied ground-troop sweep into Yugoslavia. Under one, the main
invasion force would be about 40,000 NATO troops massed in Hungary
who would head south to encircle Belgrade. Under the other, the
main invasion would come from 14,000 NATO troops already stationed
in Macedonia and an equal number in Albania. By ERIC ROSENBERG.
