<HEADLINE>
A SOMMELIER'S FAVORITES 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 c.1999 Albany Times Union  
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHESTERTOWN, N.Y. _ The following selections are good values
that Brian Sweeney is enthusiastic about:
</P>
<P>
   1996 Mer Soleil, Chardonnay (Central Coast, Calif.)
</P>
<P>
   1995 O. LeFlaive, Puligny-Montrachet, Champ Canet, Premier Cru
(Burgundy, France)
</P>
<P>
   1996 Archery Summit, Vireton, Pinot Gris Blend (Oregon)
</P>
<P>
   1996 Formentini, Pinot Grigio (Italy)
</P>
<P>
   1996 Hugel, Gewurztraminer (Alsace, France)
</P>
<P>
   1994 Anderson's Conn Valley Vineyards, Cabernet Sauvignon
Friends Lake Inn Cuvee (California.)
</P>
<P>
   1995 Staton Hills, Merlot (Washington state)
</P>
<P>
   1995 Saucelito Canyon, Zinfandel (California)
</P>
<P>
   1997 Wildhorse, Pinot Noir (California)
</P>
<P>
   1995 Chateau Fourcas-Hosten (Bordeaux, France)
</P>
<P>
   1993 Louis Jadot, Santenay, Clos de Malte, Premier Cru
(Burgundy, France)
</P>
<P>
   1995 Chante Cigale, Chateauneuf-du-Pape (Rhone, France)
</P>
<P>
   1996 Lingenfelder, Spatburgunder (Germany)
</P>
<P>
   1991 Le Ragose, Amarone della Valpolicella (Veneto, Italy)
</P>
<P>
   1991 Cune, Rioja Imperial Reserva (Rioja, Spain)
</P>
