   MOTORCOACH-RESORT (Undated) _ A few miles, as the pelican flies,
from the warm green waters of the Gulf of Mexico, tan bodies
gathered round a patio table. The conversation paused when an
engine rumble neared. A new neighbor was moving onto Southern
Breeze Drive. ``Nice,'' Kraig Brechbuhler said as the newest home
on the block rolled by, its burgundy-and-gold sides sparkling in
the noon sun. In the gated community known as Pelican Lake
Motorcoach Resort, not only do the neighbors come and go, but so
also do the homes. No Winnebagos here, however. This resort is
exclusively for luxury motor coaches, most of them longer than 37
feet. They look like tour buses for rock stars. By Diane Ketcham.
