</P>
<P>
   ANGRY SEX _ When Dad gets mad, watch out. But when Mom is upset,
no sweat. That motto has prevailed in many American families, and
now researchers have found that there is actually a universal
psychological thread to the whole phenomenon. In findings that will
hit home with families of explosive or moody fathers, a recent
study revealed that Dad's negative emotions are transmitted quickly
and powerfully throughout his immediate family.
</P>
<P>
   CIGARETTES _ Since the forced retirement of Joe Camel more than
a year ago, and the recent federal ban on tobacco billboards, big
cigarette companies have come up with new innovative ideas to reach
their consumers. Camel, Marlboro, Kool and other brands have signed
bars and clubs in all major cities around the country to exclusive
contracts. In return for their loyalty, the bars are showered with
gifts, cash, and free cigarettes. Another perk? Bartenders get free
access to all bars signed with the company in other cities.
</P>
<P>
   MILITIAS _ There is a growing movement to organize
African-Americans into armed militias, an effort that has gained
new prominence in the face of publicity about police violence
against minorities in New York. The armed militia advocates
envision a force ready to defend against police whom they believe
are no longer upholding the law but instead are disregarding the
civil rights of minorities.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE GLUT _ Inspired by the rags-to-riches stories of directors
like Spike Lee (``Do the Right Thing'') and Steven Soderbergh
(``sex, lies &AMP; videotape'') a growing number of aspiring filmmakers
are maxing out credit cards, hitting up relatives for loans and
spending trust funds in chase of the golden ring _ fame, money and
adulation.
</P>
<P>
   REFUGEES _ Like the 85,000 fellow Palestinians living in this
refugee camp north of Amman, Obeed spends a lot of time thinking
about her homeland. The disappearance of what was once Palestine
from the geopolitical maps has done little to erase its powerful
lure to these refugees who cling to their dreams of returning home.
</P>
<P>
   ETHNIC PR _ The Albanian Media Group works mostly with Albanian
clients and Albanian audiences, packaging information for ethnic
newspapers and other specialized media outlets. For decades, such
ethnic- or culture-specific marketing simply did not exist _ such
efforts were either bunched in with the mainstream or ignored
altogether. Now, as ethnic communities gain market power,
mainstream companies and organizations are realizing they need a
voice in those areas.
</P>
<P>
   BUSINESS ETHICS _ The man who wrote the ``Sullivan Principles,''
a rallying point for protests and economic sanctions against
apartheid in South Africa, is now at work on ethical guidelines for
corporations that deal with regimes considered to be corrupt or
repressive.
</P>
<P>
   THEFT BIRD _ The stuff that dreams are made of was no Maltese
falcon, it was a parrot from the Central Park Zoo.
</P>
<P>
   LIBRARIANS _ Who is that with the pierced navel and Day-Glo
hair? It's your friendly, stereotype-busting librarian.
</P>
<P>
   PATS MARCH _ Marching in the St. Patrick's Day parade in Civil
War garb.
</P>
