<SLUG> BC-HEARST-NEWS-BUDGET-1STLD-WRITETHRU-HNS </SLUG>
  
 Wednesday, April 7, 1999    
 Editors     
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Hearst News Service has filed or will file the following
stories for Thursday and Sunday. If you have questions, please call
Susie McBee or Tim Spence at 202-298-6920. For questions about
Houston Chronicle sports stories, please call 713-220-7896.
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Adds: KOSOVO-NATO; McCAIN; BORDER-GAS; TEXAS-EXPLOSIVES;
ROAD-RAGE; MICROSOFT; COMPAQ; BBN-ASTROS; BBO-AARON; and
GLF-MASTERS-DUVAL.)
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (The ``HNS'' tag appears in all sluglines.)
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   For Thursday:
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-NATO (Washington) _ President Clinton vows the NATO
alliance will continue military pressure on the Serbian-run
government of Yugoslavia, dismissing cease-fire overtures and the
possible release of three American GIs as insufficient. By
GREG-McDONALD.
</P>
<P>
   INVASION-SCENARIOS (Washington) _ Two concepts are emerging for
an allied ground-troop sweep into Yugoslavia. Under one, the main
invasion force would be about 40,000 NATO troops massed in Hungary
who would head south to encircle Belgrade. Under the other, the
main invasion would come from 14,000 NATO troops already stationed
in Macedonia and an equal number in Albania. By ERIC ROSENBERG.
</P>
<P>
   McCAIN (Washington) _ Sen. John McCain, R-Ariz., has postponed
his announcement of his campaign for the presidency, saying it
would be inappropriate during a time of conflict. But the crisis in
Yugoslavia has been the best thing to happen to the only combat
veteran and former POW among announced or likely presidential
candidates. By BENNETT ROTH. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BORDER-GAS (Laredo, Texas) _ While droves of American tourists
cross the border into Mexico in search of inexpensive liquor, food
and curios, Mexicans are driving to the U.S. side of the border for
inexpensive gasoline. A gallon of gasoline in Mexico costs about
twice as much as it does in the United States. By DANE SCHILLER.
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-EXPLOSIVES (Houston) _ A Freeport, Texas, gang known as
the Vatos Locos (``Crazy Dudes'') planned to use stolen plastic
explosives from Fort Hood to blow up the Freeport police station
and the home of a police officer, federal agents testify in hearing
for a gang member charged with drug trafficking. By MARK SMITH and
STEVE OLAFSON.
</P>
<P>
   ROAD-RAGE (Houston) _ Houston launches a program to curb
excessive speeding and aggressive driving between the rush hours to
combat road rage. By S.K. BARDWELL.
</P>
<P>
   BUSINESS/FINANCIAL NEWS (``f'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT (Houston) _ Microsoft Corp. will release Windows 98,
2nd edition, in the fall. Early reports were that the company was
going to charge $89 for the upgrade, but instead it is going to
give away all but the portion of the software that will allow
modem-to-modem networking. By DWIGHT SILVERMAN.
</P>
<P>
   COMPAQ (Houston) _ Compaq Computer Corp. joined an industry
alliance seeking to unify the fractured market for Unix, a software
operating system used to control powerful business computers. By
TRICIA SERJU-HARRIS.
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BBN-ASTROS (Houston) _ Fresh off a stirring season-opening
victory, the Houston Astros try to keep it going as they play host
to the Chicago Cubs tonight at the Astrodome. By CARLTON THOMPSON.
</P>
<P>
   With BBN-LOPEZ-COLUMN
</P>
<P>
   BBO-AARON (Undated) _ Thursday marks the 25th anniversary of
Hank Aaron's record-breaking 715th home run to shatter Babe Ruth's
longtime record. It was a turbulent time for Aaron, who enjoyed
little of the fanfare accorded to Mark McGwire and Sammy Sosa in
their record-breaking home-run race last season. By MICKEY
HERSKOWITZ.
</P>
<P>
   GLF-MASTERS-DUVAL (Augusta, Ga.) _ David Duval may be the
overwhelming favorite, but there is no shortage of contenders for
the Masters title this week at Augusta National. By EDDIE SEFKO.
</P>
<P>
   With: GLF-BLINEBURY-COLUMN
</P>
