<P>
   FAA-Y2K TEST &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ When midnight rolls around Dec. 31, Federal Aviation
Administration chief Jane Garvey will be flying from Washington,
D.C., to Los Angeles, convinced that the agency's Y2K problems are
solved and that her plane won't crash into another because of a
computer glitch. But just to make sure, Garvey will be in Denver
this weekend as the FAA conducts its first test to see whether its
air traffic control radar system is Year 2000-compatible. By G.
CHAMBERS WILLIAMS III. Story has moved in ``a'' general news
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   MIDSHIPMAN-SEX &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ Birk Billingsley's first love was the U.S.
Naval Academy, and his second, more recent, love was a freshman in
his squad. Now the 22-year-old Texan's affair with the academy
could be nearing an end because he broke the rules by having an
``unduly familiar'' relationship with Kristina Shiroma, an
underclassman also from Texas. The two have been expelled from the
academy, 25 days before Billingsley was to graduate. Their
expulsions are pending approval by the Office of the Secretary of
the Navy. By GABRIELLE CRIST. Story has moved in ``a'' general news
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   E N T E R T A I N M E N T &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   TV-PERKINS-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ HBO's ``The Sopranos'' might be the talk of TV after
13 episodes, but ``Law &AMP; Order'' is still trucking after nine
seasons. The longest-running drama on the tube recently got an
unprecedented three-season renewal. TV Critic Ken Parish Perkins
tells why. By KEN PARISH PERKINS. Story will move in ``e''
entertainment category. (Accompanied by TV-DURABILITY.) &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   POPMUSIC-FERMAN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ It's hard to feel sorry for Jeff Beck.
</P>
<P>
   Beck's lot, we're told, is a tough one. It seems ol' Jeff is
running short on money, something he has mentioned in numerous
interviews to promote his latest CD, ``Who Else!'' He says his
financial future is not stable, and that as far back as his 1995
tour with Santana he was ``desperate'' for money.
</P>
<P>
   What caused these financial woes? Drugs? Unscrupulous
management? Um, no.
</P>
<P>
   Jeff Beck is broke because Jeff Beck spent much of the past, oh,
19 years ``not working very much.'' ``Who Else!'' is only his fifth
solo CD since 1980, and his tours have been even more sporadic. By
DAVE FERMAN. Story will move in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   F O O D A N D D I N I N G &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-CHAPMAN-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ Around Sweetwater, they call Lavaughn
Freeman the Tomato Man. They do it out of admiration for his juicy
tomatoes; they wouldn't make fun of this guy. He's about
6-foot-forever and several hundred pounds. Several. Now, Freeman is
becoming a fixture in downtown Fort Worth, where he tends his
produce stand at Third and Houston streets. By ART CHAPMAN. Story
will move in ``d'' food and dining category. &QL; 
