<HEADER>
A9306 &Cx1f; tie-z
u a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-CIR-COMPUTERS-SPECIAL     04-07 0304
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CIR-COMPUTERS-SPECIAL-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TECHNOLOGY RESOURCES FOR SPECIAL-NEED CHILDREN AND THEIR PARENTS 
</HEADLINE>
  (mk) 
 By DEBRA NUSSBAUM   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Thanks to classes in public schools and programs sponsored by
community organizations, it's rare to find a disabled child or
teen-ager who hasn't logged onto a computer.
</P>
<P>
   ``Every child with a special need will be involved with
computers one way or another,'' said Bridget Lyne, managing editor
of Exceptional Parent magazine (www.eparent.com). ``The learning
possibilities, I couldn't even begin to quantify.''
</P>
<P>
   The magazine, published since 1971 as a guide for parents of
children or young adults with disabilities or health problems, has
increased its focus on technology in the past few years. A
four-part series that started in November and covered learning
software and adaptive devices can be ordered from the magazine at
(800) 372-7368.
</P>
<P>
   The Exceptional Parent 1999 Resource Guide, which is published
every January and is available in bookstores or through the
magazine for $12, also lists technology resources. Ms. Lyne
recommends checking with local public schools or night-school
programs to see if they offer technology classes.
</P>
<P>
   Goodwill Industries International (www.goodwill.org) offers
computer training and job-skills classes at about 100 offices in
the United States, said Christine Nyirjesy Bragale, a Goodwill
spokeswoman. The classes vary in price. To find the closest local
office, call (800) 664-6577.
</P>
<P>
   The Alliance for Technology Access (www.ATAccess.org), a
nonprofit group that began 11 years ago as a consumer-driven
technology and resource center, now has 40 offices across the
country. It offers information about software and other assistive
technology, and consumers can try out the equipment at its centers.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-04-07-99 1630EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
