<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BEER-NUT-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
GLORIA IN EXCELCIS BREW-O
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BRIAN MELTON 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Imagine yourself a European pilgrim garbed in heavy wool robes.
At day's end, you find an inn run by Trappist monks. You're offered
communal warmth, the safety of fellow believers and a pitcher full
of deep, rich, aromatic liquid bread.
</P>
<P>
   Say hello to Chimay ale.
</P>
<P>
   Now, imagine yourself in our kitchen. My queen puts the
finishing touches on an enormous Napa Valley-style sandwich with
smoked turkey, roasted red bell peppers, Vidalia onions and wilted
arugula on freshly baked rosemary bread, with homemade tarragon
mayonnaise and chutney mustard dressing. Then imagine washing it
all down with the same Chimay ale.
</P>
<P>
   Say hello to heaven.
</P>
<P>
   Which is as it should be, considering that Chimay ale is still
brewed by Belgian Trappist monks in the same well-considered manner
that it has been brewed in for at least 100 years. This particular
nectar comes corked with a metal cage atop an oversized bottle, and
the similarity to wine is not accidental. Belgians feel strongly
that beer is just as sophisticated a beverage as the grape
varietals of their French neighbors. And the reverence with which
they treat their brews is well-deserved.
</P>
<P>
   Chimay is unlike any beer you've come across. The murky color
results from a strong yeast presence that pleasantly permeates
every tonal quality from start to finish. Pour carefully, so that
the residue stays in the bottle. Your reward is a smooth, fruity,
rich concoction that works equally well as a delightful aperitif,
accompaniment to dinner or post-prandial toasting beverage.
</P>
<P>
   And the best part? You don't have to give yourself over to vows
of poverty, chastity and obedience _ it's already been done for
you.
</P>
<P>
   Such a deal. Oy.
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
