<HEADER>
A9359 &Cx1f; ttj-z
u d &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FUSIONFOOD-RECIPES-2T     04-07 0702
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FUSIONFOOD-RECIPES-2TAKES-HNS </SLUG>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
Chilies Rellenos With Goat Cheese, 
Currants and Cilantro
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR;
</P>
<P>
   &LR; A simplified version of a recipe in Hot Vegetables by Hugh
Carpenter (Ten Speed Press, $17.95).
</P>
<P>
   6 fresh poblano chilies &QL; 
1 red bell pepper &QL; 
\ cup pine nuts (pignoli) &QL; 
2 green onions &QL; 
{ cup corn kernels &QL; 
\ cup each: chopped cilantro leaves and dried currants &QL; 
4 ounces soft goat cheese &QL; 
{ teaspoon each: salt and Asian chili sauce &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Tomato Salsa (recipe follows) &QL; 
Place chilies and bell pepper directly over gas stovetop flames
turned to high. Char until black on all sides. Alternatively, char
under the oven broiler. When charred, transfer to a plastic bag,
seal, and allow chilies and bell pepper to steam 10 minutes. Rub
off all the charred black skin. Make a cut lengthwise along each
chili, rinse out seeds and discard, and pat chili dry with paper
towels. Stem, seed and mince bell pepper. Preheat oven to 325
degrees. Place pine nuts in single layer on baking sheet and roast
8 minutes until golden
</P>
<P>
   For stuffing: Mince green onions; combine in a bowl with chopped
bell pepper, pine nuts, corn, cilantro, currants, goat cheese, salt
and chili sauce. Mix well with your fingers. Gently fill chilies
with stuffing. Refrigerate. Prepare Tomato Salsa. Advance
preparation may be completed as long as 8 hours before serving.
</P>
<P>
   To serve: Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Heat stuffed chilies 15
minutes or until heated through. Place stuffed chilies on a plate.
Spoon Tomato Salsa around sides and serve at once.
</P>
<P>
   Tomato Salsa
</P>
<P>
   } pound tomatoes, seeded and diced &QL;
</P>
<P>
   cup minced red onion &QL; 
1 garlic clove, minced &QL; 
1 jalapeo, seeded and minced &QL; 
2 teaspoons chopped cilantro leaves &QL; 
1 tablespoon fresh lime juice &QL; 
{ teaspoon salt &QL; 
Combine tomatoes, onion, garlic, jalapeo, cilantro, lime juice and
salt. Let stand at least 30 minutes. Makes about 1{ cups.
</P>
<P>
   Stir-Fried Coconut Curry Chicken &QL; 
With Bok Choy and Basil
</P>
<P>
   From ``Fusion Food Cookbook`` by Hugh Carpenter and Teri
Sandison (Artisan, $35).
</P>
<P>
   2 whole chicken breasts (about 1{ pounds), boned and skinned &QL; 
2 tablespoons dry sherry &QL; 
1 tablespoon each: hoisin sauce and dark sesame oil &QL; 
1 small bunch bok choy &QL; 
1 red bell pepper &QL; 
5 whole green onions &QL; 
4 garlic cloves, finely minced &QL; 
1 tablespoon very finely minced fresh ginger &QL; 
Stir Fry Sauce (recipe follows) &QL; 
3 tablespoons cooking oil, divided &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Cut chicken lengthwise into 1-inch-wide strips. With your knife,
working on a sharp bias, cut each strip into [-inch-thin
rectangular pieces. Place chicken in a bowl and add sherry, hoisin
and sesame oil; mix thoroughly with your fingers. Marinate at least
15 minutes but no longer than 8 hours.
</P>
<P>
   Separate bok choy stalks. Cut each on a sharp diagonal into
1-inch lengths, turning stalk over half a turn after each cut. Set
aside 4 cups bok choy. Stem and seed bell pepper; cut into
\-inch-by-1-inch rectangles. Cut green onions on a sharp diagonal
into {-inch lengths. Combine garlic and ginger.
</P>
<P>
   Make Stir-Fry Sauce. To this point, recipe can be completed as
long as 8 hours before cooking.
</P>
<P>
   Place wok over highest heat. When very hot, add 2 tablespoons
oil. Tilt wok to coat sides with oil. When oil just begins to
smoke, add chicken and stir-fry just until it loses its raw outside
color, about 1 minute. Transfer to a platter.
</P>
<P>
   Immediately return wok to highest heat. Add remaining oil, then
add garlic mixture. Saut a few seconds, then add vegetables;
stir-fry until they brighten, about 2 minutes. Return chicken to
wok and pour in Stir Fry Sauce. When Stir Fry Sauce comes to a low
boil, taste and adjust seasonings. Transfer to 4 heated dinner
plates. Serve immediately. Makes 4 servings.
</P>
<P>
   Stir Fry Sauce
</P>
<P>
   \ cup chopped fresh basil leaves &QL;
</P>
<P>
   cup each: dry sherry and coconut milk (not cream of coconut) &QL; 
1 tablespoon each: oyster sauce, hoisin sauce, dark sesame oil and
red wine vinegar &QL; 
1 teaspoon each: cornstarch, sugar and store-bought Indian curry
paste or 1 tablespoon curry powder &QL; 
In a small bowl, combine basil, sherry, coconut milk, oyster sauce,
hoisin sauce, oil, vinegar, cornstarch, sugar and curry paste.
</P>
