<HEADER>
A9531 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-LITERARYQUIZ-TEX     04-07 0318
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LITERARY </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TEST YOUR LITERARY KNOWLEDGE
</HEADLINE>
 QUIZ-TEX (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   To celebrate the start of another major-league baseball season,
here's a puzzler featuring classic works spinning off the national
pastime _ fiction and nonfiction, some reportage, and a
111-year-old poem. Simply match the titles with their authors. You
pass with nine correct answers (the customary simple majority) and
attain an A with 12 right. Score yourself an extra point if you can
identify the work that anticipated by almost 20 years Bill Veeck's
employment of a midget as pinch batter in an official American
League game. Answers are on the opposite page. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The titles: &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1. ``Bang the Drum Slowly'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   2. ``Baseball Hattie'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   3. ``The Boys of Summer'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   4. ``Casey at the Bat'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   5. ``The Glory of Their Times'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   6. ``The Great American Novel'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   7. ``Hub Fans Bid Kid Adieu'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   8. ``The Kid From Tomkinsville'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   9. ``The Long Season'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   10. ``The Natural'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   11. ``Pitching in a Pinch'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   12. ``The Red-Headed Outfield'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   13. ``Shoeless Joe'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   14. ``The Summer Game'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   15. ``Ball Four'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   16. ``You Could Look It Up'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Their authors: &QL;
</P>
<P>
   a. Roger Angell &QL;
</P>
<P>
   b. Jim Bouton &QL;
</P>
<P>
   c. Jim Brosnan &QL;
</P>
<P>
   d. Zane Grey &QL;
</P>
<P>
   e. Mark Harris &QL;
</P>
<P>
   f. Roger Kahn &QL;
</P>
<P>
   g. W.P. Kinsella &QL;
</P>
<P>
   h. Bernard Malamud &QL;
</P>
<P>
   i. Christy Mathewson &QL;
</P>
