<P>
   GLF-MASTERS-LICKLITER _ As a golfer at Wright State, Frank
Lickliter of Franklin and his college teammates were stopped at the
gate of Augusta National. They just wanted to visit the pro shop
but were told no. Instead, a guard took their orders for Master's
tournament hats and brought them out to the street. My, how things
have changed for Lickliter, who is preparing to tee off in his
first-ever Master's tournament Thursday morning. He finished 1998
among the top 10 money winners and won an invitation to Augusta. We
talk with his parents, golfing coaches and buddies in Franklin and
Wright State about Lickliter, who last month remembered where he
started by equipping his old high school team with new jackets.
(Jackson/Budd, Dayton Daily News). 18.
</P>
