   GLF-MASTERS-NUHN _ AUGUSTA, Ga. _ Column on Frank Lickliter, the
Franklin native who is playing in the Masters. (Nuhn, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 20-25.
</P>
<P>
   NFL
</P>
<P>
   FBN-NFLDRAFT-TACKLES _ There are as many as 14 tackles taken in
the first two rounds. Why has this become a premiere position?
(Pasquarelli, Atlantra Journal-Constitution) 20.
</P>
<P>
   FOOTBALL
</P>
<P>
   FBC-UGA-JASPER _ Jasper Sanks entered Georgia last season as one
of the most highly-publicized running backs in recent history. Many
fans thought that he might be the savior of the team at running
back, but he battled weight problems, was injured for most of the
season and was considered a major disappointment. Sanks entered
spring drills as a new player, losing nearly 20 pounds and
regaining the speed and quickness that made him a high school
All-American at Carver High in Columbus. After a frustrating
freshman year, Sanks hopes to have a better season as a sophomore.
(Towers, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20. WITH PHOTO. MOVED.
</P>
