<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Thursday, April 8, and thereafter. The stories will carry the
``f'' financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For
questions about stories, contact Jeremy Bagott at the Daily News,
(818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-REVOLT (Los Angeles) _ Tales of movie crews leaving
Hollywood turned out to be true as off-lot location shooting of
movies in Los Angeles County was down 21 percent in the first
quarter. March shoots fell 27 percent. The movie decline was mostly
offset by increases in TV activity, with overall production sliding
just 2.9 percent in the first quarter.
</P>
<P>
   By Dave McNary. (Will move in the ``n'' California and ``f''
financial news file.)
</P>
<P>
   MILK-PRICE (Los Angeles) _ Even as gasoline prices soar, the
cost of one semi-precious fluid has dropped dramatically in the
last week. Thanks to a state-mandated cut in wholesale prices
charged by California dairies, the price for a gallon of milk has
fallen by about 50 cents per gallon at the largest grocery chains
operating in Los Angeles and Ventura counties.
</P>
<P>
   By Ben Sullivan. (Will move in the ``f'' financial and ``n''
California news file.)
</P>
