<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Thursday, April 8, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Jeremy Bagott at the Daily News, (818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   SCHOOLS-UNION (Los Angeles) _ The United Teachers Los Angeles
pushed legislation Wednesday that charter school principals and
teachers alike say would cripple their efforts by forcing teachers
into the union. They say it would handcuff charter schools in the
San Fernando Valley by giving the union power over of teacher
assignments and demotions and remove merit pay for teachers who
excel. By Terri Hardy and Michael Coit. (Will move in the ``n''
California news file.)
</P>
<P>
   LA-POW (Los Angeles) _ With word that Staff Sgt. Andrew Ramirez
and two other American prisoners of war will be released, his East
Los Angeles neighborhood erupted in celebration. Ramirez's cousin,
Olivia Rodriguez, said President Clinton called the soldier's
mother, Vivian Ramirez, on Easter Sunday to console her. By Yvette
Cabrera. (Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news
file.)
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-REVOLT (Los Angeles) _ Tales of movie crews leaving
Hollywood turned out to be true as off-lot location shooting of
movies in Los Angeles County was down 21 percent in the first
quarter. March shoots fell 27 percent. The movie decline was mostly
offset by increases in TV activity, with overall production sliding
just 2.9 percent in the first quarter.
</P>
<P>
   By Dave McNary. (Will move in the ``n'' California and ``f''
financial news file.)
</P>
<P>
   MILK-PRICE (Los Angeles) _ Even as gasoline prices soar, the
cost of one semi-precious fluid has dropped dramatically in the
last week. Thanks to a state-mandated cut in wholesale prices
charged by California dairies, the price for a gallon of milk has
fallen by about 50 cents per gallon at the largest grocery chains
operating in Los Angeles and Ventura counties.
</P>
<P>
   By Ben Sullivan. (Will move in the ``f'' financial and ``n''
California news file.)
</P>
