   BUSINESS/FINANCIAL NEWS (``f'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT (Houston) _ Microsoft Corp. will release Windows 98,
2nd edition, in the fall. Early reports were that the company was
going to charge $89 for the upgrade, but instead it is going to
give away all but the portion of the software that will allow
modem-to-modem networking. By DWIGHT SILVERMAN. (Already filed.)
</P>
