   FLA-ELDERLY-VOTERS (Deerfield Beach, Fla.) _ When the wave of
retirees moved to South Florida during the condominium booms of the
1960s and 1970s, they brought their machine politics with them.
Their condo associations and social clubs were just like the
meeting halls and church basements back home, and they became a
steady, swelling political force, and they voted for Democrats. But
now the New Deal Democrats are being replaced by immigrants from
Latin America, the Caribbean, Canada, Europe, as well as American
blacks and younger, working people. ``Between now and 2010, the
Democratic Party will be losing its most stable and loyal core,''
said a political scientist. By Rick Bragg. (The story has moved in
``a'' news file.)
