<SLUG> BC-STEAKOUT08-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Steak take-out chain beefs up expansion plans
 &HT;    By Shelia M. Poole
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Steak-Out Franchising Inc. is branching out to other
regions and perhaps other countries in an aggressive expansion
plan.
</P>
<P>
   ``We are basically looking at going into new markets outside of
the South,'' Don Harkleroad, president and CEO, said Wednesday.
``We think the concept is solidly proven, and now we have the
infrastructure to the point where we can support the growth.''
</P>
<P>
   The company, which operates a full-meal delivery system
specializing in steak, has 35 units under development in Colorado,
Kansas and Texas. Other markets under consideration include New
York, New Jersey and Minnesota. The company said it has had
inquiries about overseas expansion.
</P>
<P>
   There are 79 Steak-Out Charbroiled Delivery stores. The company
offers catering and takeout.
</P>
<P>
   The business was formed in 1988, and Harkleroad acquired it
several years later.
</P>
<P>
   But Harkleroad said the company, which has revenues of $62
million, plans to build on its base in this region. Plans call for
another 26 stores in the Southeast, with eight in metro Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   The company also plans to move its training facility from
Columbia, S.C., to metro Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
