<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-07 21:18 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A9813 &Cx1f; ttj-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BKN-Rockets-Price-HNS     04-07 0749
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-Rockets-Price-HNS </SLUG>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
Rockets guard Price has cartilage surgery
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; By MICHAEL MURPHY &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; c. 1999, Houston Chronicle &LR;  &QL; 
Price
</P>
<P>
   Rockets point guard Brent Price underwent surgery Wednesday to
repair torn cartilage in his right knee and is expected to be back
in time for the playoffs.
</P>
<P>
   While it was thought that Matt Maloney would be activated off
the injured list, the Rockets did not make a move Wednesday to fill
Price's roster spot. They are expected to announce a move before
today's game against the San Antonio Spurs at Compaq Center.
</P>
<P>
   Price hurt his knee in Tuesday's 111-74 victory over Golden
State, tearing the right lateral meniscus on the last play of the
first half when he landed awkwardly after making a pass to Scottie
Pippen.
</P>
<P>
   Team physicians Walter Lowe and Bruce Moseley performed the
30-minute surgery Wednesday morning, finding a tear that was larger
than anticipated.
</P>
<P>
   ``Brent's surgery went well,'' Lowe said. ``This was a pretty
big tear. It was pretty much how the MRI looked, but it was a tear
that had caused a flap (of tissue) that could catch between the two
bones _ flip back and forth between them.
</P>
<P>
   ``So it was one that definitely needed to come out. It was
definitely not a repairable tear. What you do is take out the torn
part of it and leave as much good cartilage as you can. It was
probably 15 or 20 percent of that cartilage (removed with the
tear), so it was a pretty significant cartilage tear.''
</P>
<P>
   The increased severity of the tear may not add any other time to
Price's recovery schedule. There is a possibility he could be back
in two weeks, which is how long it took Charles Barkley to return
from a similar _ if less severe _ cartilage tear in his left knee.
</P>
<P>
   ``There was nothing to really slow him down,'' Lowe said. ``As
long as he doesn't swell. It's going to be a little tougher than a
small tear like Charles had, but from the way he's recovered from
some other (injuries), he could still hold to a pretty quick
(recovery) time frame.''
</P>
<P>
   Price missed the 1994-95 season with a torn anterior cruciate
ligament in his left knee. Price's first season in Houston
(1996-97) was marred by a broken bone in his left arm and a torn
ACL in his left knee, injuries that limited him to 25 games.
</P>
<P>
   Lowe said Price wasn't in the best of spirits, but wasn't overly
depressed about suffering yet another injury.
</P>
<P>
   ``Well, I think it's good his dad (Denny Price) was in town,
because Denny is a pretty level-headed guy,'' Lowe said.
</P>
<P>
   ``Brent wasn't the most excited guy I've ever seen this morning,
but he's pretty experienced with this stuff. I guess you have to
use the old adage, he took it in stride. He was sitting up, awake
in the recovery room last time I saw him, saying, `Oh, I guess it's
time to get to work.'
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't think he was as bummed as he would have been had this
been a new tear of an ACL (anterior cruciate ligament) or some
injury that would have a prolonged recovery, but I still don't
think he had the greatest day.''
</P>
<P>
   Price had scored double figures in the three games before
Tuesday's victory over Golden State and had made 14 of 26 3-point
attempts over the last nine games.
</P>
<P>
   ``I just thought Brent was playing really, really positive
basketball and was a big asset for us,'' coach Rudy Tomjanovich
said. ``This happens to a lot of teams _ we've seen this all over
the league. We just have to do the best we can to step up.
</P>
<P>
   ``I really feel for him. He came here as a free agent, looked at
the system and thought it was a good place for him.
</P>
<P>
   ``But a couple days into our first year here, I think it was our
third practice, he goes down (with the broken bone in his arm). And
then he works his way back and gets hurt again (left knee).
</P>
<P>
   ``He was really getting into a groove, had his role defined and
was doing a real good job at it. But it's not over. He's a tough
guy. He could still be back and still be a positive for us.''
</P>
<P>
   Scottie Pippen hopes players like Bryce Drew and Maloney will be
able to pick up the slack in Price's absence.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's going to be hard to replace what Brent does for this
ballclub, because he really goes after the ball so hard,'' Pippen
said.
</P>
<P>
   ``But we have some young guys like Bryce, who has been waiting
for this opportunity to get out there and play. He is going to have
to find some type niche where he is able to help this ballclub
right now. I think he will.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
