   KOSOVO-LOGO (Undated) _ Even wars have logos these days, at
least on television, and the coverage of the Kosovo war invariably
features the Albanian eagle, splashed across the screen like the
NBC peacock. The Albanian eagle, angular, Gothic, almost medieval
in style, with its two heads and dragonlike claws, seems to sum up
the ancient nature of the conflicts in the Balkans _ and the fears
Americans have of an area they don't understand. It's a feathered
version of all the fears of foreign entanglements we've worried
about since Washington's Farewell address. By Phil Patton.
