<HEADLINE>
TIMES NAMES NEW V.P. FOR ADVERTISING SALES 
</HEADLINE>
  (sw) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Thomas E. Helling, group director for the corporate
and financial advertising teams at The New York Times, was named
vice president for advertising sales on Wednesday. In his new
position, Helling, 42, will be responsible for overseeing a wide
range of advertising categories at The Times, including financial
services, media, packaged goods, technology and books.
</P>
